HEADWORD: Sifter
<hw>Sift"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, sifts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any lamellirostral bird, as a
duck or goose; -- so called because it sifts or strains its food from
the water and mud by means of the lamell<?/ of the beak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sig</ent>⟦br⟧
